        "<p>But the rest offended herâ€”and inarguably because it wasnâ€™t a gesture</p>\n<p>but an emotion. She was appalled by West Egg, this unprecedented</p>\n<p>â€œplaceâ€ that Broadway had begotten upon a Long Island fishing</p>\n<p>villageâ€”appalled by its raw vigour that chafed under the old</p>\n<p>euphemisms and by the too obtrusive fate that herded its inhabitants</p>\n<p>along a shortcut from nothing to nothing. She saw something awful in</p>\n<p>the very simplicity she failed to understand.</p>",
