        "<p>whose head made damp the pyjama pocket over his heart!</p>\n<p>â€¦ Through the hall of the Buchanansâ€™ house blew a faint wind, carrying</p>\n<p>the sound of the telephone bell out to Gatsby and me as we waited at</p>\n<p>the door.</p>\n<p>â€œThe masterâ€™s body?â€ roared the butler into the mouthpiece. â€œIâ€™m</p>\n<p>sorry, madame, but we canâ€™t furnish itâ€”itâ€™s far too hot to touch this</p>\n<p>noon!â€</p>",
